            :markdown
                My friend [Tim] got a gig as the public address announcer for the Michigan club lacrosse team. One thing lead to another, and it lead to him starting up [GreatLaxState]. I may have done some slight assistance on the layout.

                We found that lacrosse was sort of lacking in the sports analytics department. At least in terms of something you could find online. We worked with some people to develop the algorithms then started working on the site.

                Version 1.0 was built in [CakePHP] and required us to find all the box scores and manually input stats, which we did for all of the 2012 season.

                Version 2.0 is mainly the current version, which is built on Rails and hosted on [Heroku]. The biggest improvement came from creating a nightly job that automatically parsed boxscores and updated the statistics. This freed up time from data entry to actually work on features.

                The next steps involve:

                *   Data Visualizations

                *   Useful player metrics and rankings

                *   Conference statistics and breakdowns

                *   Improved prediction algorithm

