                =link_to 'Broke Student Film Festival', 'http://brokestudentfilmfestival.com'
            :markdown
                This was a project for my brother and his fiancé (note: update this 5/2015). They were having issues with the website for the film festival they were organizing. I offered to step in and help.

                They didn't have any hosting and didn't particularly want to spend a lot of time hacking code, so it needed to be something easy so that I wouldn't need to do that much work.

                I decided to use [Middleman] as the CMS, which allowed me to use markdown to write most of the content. I was then add them as contributors to repo on [Github] and have them use [Prose.io] to edit the content. Whenever a change is pushed, it kicks of a [TravisCI] build that will build the distribution and upload it to [S3] where the project is hosted.

